 New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If individuals are dissatisfied </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">following an investigation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, then the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">‘quality’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of those investigations is suspect.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The main reason for our dissatisfaction is the systematic manipulation and denial of the facts by PHSO in order to find no case to answer or minimize the case against the public body concerned and their total lack of accountability when their poor decision making is criticised.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In 2010 – 2011</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> PHSO found in favour of 1.45% of complainants.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> In 2011 – 2012 PHSO found in favour of 1.4% of complaints, therefore it is unsurprising that 64% of the public expressed the view that making a complaint would not make a difference. They were right. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is little point using resources to encourage more people to make a complaint when the Ombudsman service is clearly unable to deliver justice and remedy to the vast majority of those who already do. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We would like to share some information with the Committee to supplement the answers given by Dame Julie Mellor and provide a more complete picture.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> We would appreciate some feedback from the Committee on the points we raise.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mr. Jenkin and Mr Hopkins both asked a series of questions concerning staff reactions to change within the organisation.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Mr. Jenkin asked particularly about ‘internal resistance’ to the reorganisation.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Dame Julie Mellor gave the impression that the staff were fully supportive, but PHSO Pressure Group understand that the recent staff survey confirms that only 10% of staff feel change is managed effectively and only 16% feel that senior management provide effective leadership. You may wish to discuss the results of the staff survey in more detail with the Ombudsman. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Dame Julie Mellor talked about changes to the Executive Team and other alterations to senior management in order to improve service delivery.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Given that PHSO are attempting to increase the number of investigations in order to provide ‘more impact for more people’ would it not be appropriate to increase the number of assessors and reduce the extremely ‘top heavy’ management structure which can be seen in this chart.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="https://dub121.mail.live.com/default.aspx?id=64855#!/mail/ViewOfficePreview.aspx?messageid=5b0a3d4d-67eb-11e3-9451-002264c28130&amp;folderid=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000&amp;attindex=0&amp;cp=-1&amp;attdepth=0&amp;n=613205312"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://dub121.mail.live.com/default.aspx?id=64855#!/mail/ViewOfficePreview.a